# 📊 Exploratory Analysis of Academic Performance Factors

## 🔍 Overview
This project investigates key factors influencing student academic performance using statistical analysis and data modeling techniques. The goal is to identify meaningful relationships between behavioral and socioeconomic variables and academic outcomes.

## 🎯 Objectives
- Analyze factors affecting student GPA
- Identify significant predictors using statistical methods
- Build interpretable models for potential predictive applications

## 🧠 Key Skills Demonstrated
- Data Cleaning & Preprocessing
- Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
- Statistical Modeling (Linear Regression)
- Hypothesis Testing
- Data Visualization
- Reproducible Research

## ⚙️ Tools & Technologies
- R (dplyr, ggplot2)
- R Markdown
- Excel (data handling)

## 📈 Methodology
- Collected dataset of 500+ students
- Cleaned and processed raw data
- Performed EDA to identify trends and correlations
- Built regression models and validated assumptions
- Conducted hypothesis testing (p < 0.05)

## 📊 Key Findings
- Study habits strongly influence academic performance
- Balanced extracurricular activities correlate with higher GPA
- Statistically significant predictors identified

## 🚀 Applications in AI
- Feature selection for predictive models
- Training datasets for education-focused AI systems
- Pattern recognition in behavioral data

